The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Advani, Sethi in 7-member team 

New Delhi: National champion Pankaj Advani and seven-time world champion Geet Sethi would join defending champion Devendra Joshi in the seven-member Indian team for the Asian billiards championship to be held in Pune from February 19-26. 

The other members of the team are Ashok Shandilya, B. Bhaskar, Sourav Kothari and Rishabh Thakkar. 

Joshi received a direct entry by virtue of being the defending champion and hence India could field an additional player, selection committee member and Billiards and Snooker Federation of India (BSFI) vice president Ravi Tandon said on Wednesday. The team was decided following a selection-cum-coaching camp held in Mumbai, he said, adding the criteria for making the grade was the points earned by them during last month?s national championship and the camp. (PTI) 




